page.title: 01GAZETTER - WOKINGHAM WITHOUT
page.content: A{semi-rural}area to the south of Wokingham. One of{attractive scenery: extensive pinewoods and rhododendrons flourishing in light sandy soil. The north-western part contains a small {industrial estate}while the north-east is mainly{agricultural}with older type houses and cottages, some dating from 16th and 17th centuries.The rest of the area consists mostly of{market- {gardening}farms with the major housing areas in the eastern section - most houses built after 1950.{New housing {estates}are now being built and some of the pinewoods are disappearing. Large houses built in the 19th century are now used as schools or have been converted into flats.To the south lies part of the eccliastical parish of St.Sebastian's. There is a small church erected in 1864:beside it the aided church school of the same time.
